<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625219>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Mycale (Aegogropila) antiae sp. nov. Habitus and details of the external appearance. A: Base masive-conical without branching (Paratype 5: FoRdeF-05-050417); B: Conical bases gathered around the papillae of C. penicillus (Paratype 2: FoRdeF-02-050417); C–D: Large specimens with profuse branching (C: Paratypes 19–20: FoRdeF-19-050417- FoRdeF-20- 050417; D: Paratype 18: FoRdeF-18-050417); E: Large sponge with branches anchored to the gorgonia L. lusitanica (Paratype 3: FoRdeF-03-050417); F: Osculum in sponge fixed in 70% Ethanol (Paratype 12: FoRdeF-12-050417); G: Subectosomal canals in live sponge in the laboratory (Paratype 3: FoRdeF-03-050417); H: Subectosomal canals in sponge fixed in 70% Ethanol (Paratype 16: FoRdeF-16-050417); J: Surface with multispicular tangential reticulation and subectosomal yellow spots—trichodragmata clusters—(Holotype)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625219/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625231>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Mycale (Aegogropila) antiae sp. nov. SEM and Micro-CT images of skeleton of the Holotype (FoRdeF-00- 160317) (Figs. A, B, C, D, F, H, J) and Paratype 1 (FoRdeF-01-160317) (Figs. E, G): A: Inhalant pores (ostia) in the areas of the reticulum of the ectosomal membrane; B: Rosettes under the tangential reticulation of the ectosome (arrows); C-D-F: Spicular tracts of different sizes and connections; E–G: Skeletal structure of the complete specimen and hard structures of its base attachment; H: Arrangement of the mycalostyles in anosculum; J: Feathery plurispicular fan-like bundle with a rosette. (Abbreviations. p: tubes of the polychaete Sabellaria alcocki; v: Ferruca stroemia; h: Hiatella arctica)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625231/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625229>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Mycale (Aegogropila) antiae sp. nov. Size distribution of spicules of the Holotype (FoRdeF-00-160317): A: Mycalostyles lengths (n = 220); B: Palmate anisochelae I lengths (n = 150); C: Mycalostyles shaft and head width (n = 60); D: Palmate anisochelae II and III lengths (n = 50 & 50); E: Raphides and trichodragmata lengths (n = 120 & 60); F: Microxeas lengths (n = 350); G: Microxeas maximum and minimum length and number of microxeas per microxeadragmata (n = 15); H: Rosettes diameter of the palmate anisochelae I and number of anisochelae per rosette (n = 18)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625229/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625221>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Mycale (Aegogropila) antiae sp. nov. SEM images of spicules mycalostyles of the Holotype (FoRdeF-00- 160317). A–F: Different length and width of mycalostyles. A: 380 x 8.8 µm, B: 363.6 x 9.0 µm, C: 353.7 x 6.2 µm, D: 318 x 4.0 µm, E: 278.2 x 1.9 µm, F: 238.7 x 1.0 µm; G–N: Different sizes of mycalostyles head; O–R: Mycalostyles head deformed." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625221/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625223>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Mycale (Aegogropila) antiae sp. nov. SEM images of spicules palmate anisochelae of the Holotype (FoRdeF-00- 160317): A–G: Palmate anisochelae I; H–N: Palmate anisochelae II; O–X: Palmate anisochelae III; Y: Spicular biometry of palmate anisochelae I; Z: Spicular biometry of the foot of palmate anisochelae I." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625223/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625227>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Mycale (Aegogropila) antiae sp. nov. SEM images of spicules of the Holotype (FoRdeF-00-160317): A: Raphides of trichodragmata scattered; B: Cluster of trichodragmata of a yellow spot; C–E: Microxeadragmata (microxeas in dragmata); F: Rosettes of palmate anisochelae I; G: Trichodragmata in formation." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625227/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625225>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Mycale (Aegogropila) antiae sp. nov. SEM images of spicules raphides and microxeas of the Holotype (FoRdeF- 00-160317): A–B: Raphides; C–D: Trichodragma and detail of an end; E–F: Terminal ends of raphides; G–N: Different sizes of microxeas; O–P: Microxeas; R: Bundle of microxeas disintegrate; S: Trichodragma in formation; T. Possible microxeadragma in formation." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625225/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625235>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Mycale (Aegogropila) antiae sp. nov. Micro-CT images of skeleton of the Holotype (FoRdeF-00-160317) (Figs. L–N) and skeleton and exhalant and inhalant canals of the Paratype 9 (FoRdeF-09-050417) (Figs. A–K): A: Scanned branching end; B-C-D-F: Transverse and longitudinal sections of the arrangement of the exhalant and inhalant canals. E-G-H-J-K: Transverse and longitudinal sections of the skeletal arrangement; L–M: Divergent feathery tracts of mycalostyles supporting the ectosomal skeleton; N: Trichodragmata (yellow spots) clusters under the ectosome (arrow)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625235/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

